<subSubSection id="D42AC3CF0D5795EED8B9DFF416E2B155" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="387B829D18246D719A6C391B05315882" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C63EF92914DA6E731345D6EA7626D832" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">
Least Concern (LC). Bidoup Nui Ba National Park is located on Central highland of Vietnam. It covers ca. 700.38 km2 and is the core zone of the Langbiang biosphere reserve (
<bibRefCitation id="134A635AF54DADFCE10A60BECF1A5281" author="Bidoup Nui Ba National Park" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Thailand" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" publicationUrl="http://bidoupnuiba.gov.vn/en/introduction-menu.html" refId="B4" refString="Bidoup Nui Ba National Park, 2016-onwards. official website., http://bidoupnuiba.gov.vn/en/introduction-menu.html" title="official website" url="http://bidoupnuiba.gov.vn/en/introduction-menu.html" year="2016 - onwards">Bidoup-Nui Ba National Park 2016</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="A2E79843101F6920B4B40EBF3BBE2903" authorityName="Tagane &amp; V. S. Dang" authorityYear="2017" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loranthaceae" genus="Macrosolen" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Macrosolen bidoupensis" order="Santalales" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bidoupensis">
<emphasis id="37C630E42A92E1CF1B54FB6FCC07B590" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Macrosolen bidoupensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is commonly found in the lower montane evergreen forest in the national park. Since the forest is widely seen and well-protected, we suggest this status as LC according to 
<bibRefCitation id="0860E62AC708904A25BD3534A39324DF" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="IUCN, Gland and Cambridge" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refId="B12" refString="IUCN, 2012. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: version 3.1. second edition. IUCN, Gland and Cambridge" title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: version 3.1. second edition" year="2012">IUCN (2012)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1D6A5F01ED3CE1E71D8C8D1368471800" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" type="notes">
<paragraph id="5DE2CFB9B87EDB6ED7EE880342995F75" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E99C9A2B2406284CFCC47DF12D2B8756" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">
